Time flies like an arrow  fruit flies like a banana.

But Somehow, we’ve officially made it to 2023. 

And as with every year, there’s a whole new CRAP of New Year’s resolutions 
“How to be a better version of ourselves, how to improve our lives, or how to make the best of it blah blah blah.

And at the end, we do improve as much as the new iPhone improves every year. 

We improve as much as Tim Tebow improved through his entire career, very little or nothing. 
Remember, the only people that have really improved through the years are The Kardashian.

Take a look of a a photo of The Kardashian family before the “update” and and look ay them now. 

Fake Empire

For most of us, “getting out there” and meeting new people is not an easy task. And saying “I found my Tribe” out loud is a bold declaration at any time of your life let alone in your 40’s.
Well, I’m lucky enough to say I found mine @venicevintagemotoclub

I’ve been swapping left and right until I’ve found a Matched and it has been a process: learning, getting to know each other, on top of that they do have an accent, an American accent 🤣. 
To me, the only thing close to it, is my brothers back home from the TUD.

Now, I’ll try to rise to the occasion

Love

Watching him grow and thrive within the biker community has been an incredible experience. Here’s to many more adventures on the open road! 🏍️ #motorcycleclub #brotherhood #rideordie #rideboundless

Falling in love happens so rarely. Oh boy, is like finding a unicorn riding a rainbow, is like finding a democrat voter in the OC area 😍 but when you do, yup can feel it in your gut (im talking about love not democrats) 
How many times I’ve heard Im looking for my “Ride or Die”. Thats how I felt the first time I saw @venicevintagemotoclub 😍 
It was love at firstly sight.

I’ve tried to play it cool at first and mustered all the courage to approach them…We met, we chatted we ride and that was it….my heart was on Fire like in the song. Crazy in love smitten. 

So if you ever find yourself in the same position, falling in love at first sight with someone or something…embrace it. Don’t be afraid, who knows it might be the 🦄 you were looking for, your Ride or Die.

ODE TO @david_olivera_cine 

Oh, my dear, it’s time to say goodbye
And I cannot and I won’t shed a tear or two
For all the pictures we shared, you and I

From Spain to New York, and now in L.A. 
You’ve been behind the lenses all that time 
And bro We do have had fun

We still have things undone
We’ve traveled far and wide, explored new lands
We have made memories that will last a lifetime.

But now the time has come to say goodbye
I know that our paths will cross again someday
So, thank you for being there through thick and thin
For sharing your dreams and your talent with me.

Farewell, my friend, and may your journey be blessed
With love, joy, and peace that never fades away
And know that wherever you go, you are missed
But please if you need a place to crashed don’t call me. 😂😂😂😂

Todo tiene un principio y todo tiene un final.…..Qué difícil es decir adiós!!

Cuánto cuesta dejar atrás algo que te hace feliz. 

Cuánto duele separarse de algo y alguien que te gusta y te hace reír. Sin embargo, lo hago con el corazón lleno. Gracias por estar, por ser…

Gracias por existir, porque no sería quién soy sin todos y cada uno de vosotros.

El tiempo y la juventud nos han saludado desde el recuerdo, y la nostalgia. Nos hemos dejado embriagar de tristeza y melancolía pero también con muchas risas, recuerdos y ron con cola. 

Por eso mismo cuesta, cuesta muchísimo decir adiós. 

La magia de decir adiós rara vez se ve en el momento en el que lo hacemos. La magia está en todo lo que hemos vivido juntos estos días. 

Así que no, no es fácil saber deciros adiós, así que mejor digo OS QUIERO MUCHO, MUCHÍSIMO.
